<HL>
   Business Brief -- Borden Inc.:
   Two Plants Are to Be Built
   For a Total of $70 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
05/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   BN
</CO>
<LP>
   Borden Inc., a New York-based producer of foods, nonfood
consumer products, and packaging and industrial products,
said it plans to build two plants for a total of $70 million
to produce pasta and food-service products.
   The $50 million pasta plant in St. Louis will have the
capacity to produce 250 million pounds a year. Production
there is to begin in late 1991, with employment expected to
exceed 200.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The $20 million food-service facililty in Jackson, Miss.,
will process or package individual-portion products, as well
as bulk-sized oil-based items, with operations scheduled to
begin in the 1990 fourth quarter. The plant will have about
400 employees when fully operational.
   Borden had 1989 world-wide sales of $7.6 billion.
</TEXT>
